Channel flow with isothermal particles, no gravity and constant density. Flow is periodic in the y- and z-directions with inflow and outflow in the x-direction. See Peng, C., Kong, B., Zhou, J., Sun, B., Passalacqua, A., Subramaniam, S., & Fox, R. O. (2019). Implementation of pseudo-turbulence closures in an Eulerian–Eulerian two-fluid model for non-isothermal gas–solid flow. Chemical Engineering Science, 207, 663-671.
